From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 18:45:00 +0800
Subject: Spoof ICE candidate IP addresses to prevent WebRTC IP leaks

When PureCloak is configured with --fingerprint-webrtc-ip, host
ICE candidates created in Port::AddAddress() will have their IP
address replaced with the spoofed value.

This prevents WebRTC-based IP leaks that can reveal the real local
IP address even when behind a proxy, since WebRTC can bypass proxy
settings for peer-to-peer connections. By replacing host candidate
IPs with a spoofed value, the real IP is never exposed through
ICE/STUN signaling.

The port number is preserved so connectivity is not affected.
Only host candidates (type kHost/c.is_local()) are spoofed, which
are the ones that leak real local IPs.

---
 third_party/webrtc/p2p/base/port.cc | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/webrtc/p2p/base/port.cc b/third_party/webrtc/p2p/base/port.cc
--- a/third_party/webrtc/p2p/base/port.cc
+++ b/third_party/webrtc/p2p/base/port.cc
@@ -51,6 +51,12 @@
 #include "rtc_base/socket_address.h"
 #include "rtc_base/span_helpers.h"
 #include "rtc_base/string_encode.h"
+
+// PureCloak: WebRTC IP spoofing for anti-fingerprinting
+#include "purecloak/common/buildflags.h"
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+#include "purecloak/common/purecloak_seed.h"
+#endif
 #include "rtc_base/string_utils.h"
 #include "rtc_base/strings/string_builder.h"
 #include "rtc_base/trace_event.h"
@@ -244,6 +250,18 @@ void Port::AddAddress(const SocketAddress& address,
   c.set_related_address(related_address);
   c.set_network_slice(network_->network_slice());
 
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+  // PureCloak: spoof host candidate IP to prevent WebRTC IP leak
+  if (c.is_local()) {
+    const auto& spoofed_ip =
+        purecloak::PureCloakSeed::GetInstance()->webrtc_ip();
+    if (!spoofed_ip.empty()) {
+      SocketAddress spoofed_addr(spoofed_ip, c.address().port());
+      c.set_address(spoofed_addr);
+    }
+  }
+#endif
+
   bool pending = MaybeObfuscateAddress(c, is_final);
 
   if (!pending) {
